<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12203e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12203e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12203e"> 203(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ hutte &agrave; viande / finish killing / ritual spit</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[story: <i>La peur sacr&eacute;e des esprits de la brousse</i>]</font>: &Eacute;tant revenu &agrave; la hutte &agrave; viande, il dit &agrave; <font color="green">[son]</font> fr&egrave;re: &ldquo;je me disposais &agrave; puiser de l&apos;eau, lorsque l&apos;eau m&apos;a interpell&eacute; <font color="green">[en disant]</font>: oh! il m&apos;a puis&eacute;e! oh! il m&apos;a puis&eacute;e! Alors, je me suis mis &agrave; courir et la for&ecirc;t a ri.&rdquo; <font color="green">[Son]</font> fr&egrave;re lui dit: &ldquo;Lance au loin les crachats rituels, car tu est pris par la peur.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[Back at the meat hut, he told his brother: &ldquo;I wanted to get some water, but the water told me &ldquo;Oh, he has taken me! he has taken me!&rdquo; So I ran into the forest and that laughed at me.&rdquo; His brother told him, launch the ritual spittle, because you have been taken by fear.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 22</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
